33. optimi viri: a form oi address commonly ironical, though not so here. In C. M. 39 Cato addresses Scipio and Laelius as optimi adulescentes. —quamquam ille quidem: nciam letitie γε; ci. 97. Quamquam seems to imply that Laelius did not altogether agree with Scipio on this subject. - expediret: se. utrique. — sentiretur: sc. ab utraque. - saepe: probably to be taken with mutari, not with dicebat, so that alias...alias is an expansion or explanation oi saepe. For alias see u. on 1. — exemplum etc: in exemplum ca- plebat ex similitudine there is the same kind oi pleonasm as above, , suaet causae allegendi praefectae. — praetexta toga: n. on r.
